<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
This idea of unlootable unless you get experience may weed out some of the farmers, but it will also weed out any of the casual gamers who want the item, heard about it, then treked to get it.  But now they are not allowed to have it simply because they are too high of a level?<P>I think the number of farmers is much smaller than the number of people who are just looking for one of the items, but to weed out the farmers we attack everyone.<P>Also, couldn't the farmers just get around this by finding the optimum level, and then just ensure that charcter doesn't advance by letting them get killed a couple of times,loosing EXP, etc. then going back to their farming?<P>However, I do like the idea of random wandering monsters with random drop loot.  This is more traditional role playing.... you do not read very often of a group that sits wating for an enemy to continually reappear so they can battle.<P>However, how would you handle the trains caused by these wandering monsters cruising by and jumping you?
</FONT>
